    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-24T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-24T01:00:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/705: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Castle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-24T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >February 24, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 24—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Repeat to London.<note n="43" xml:id="d26fn43">Transmitted to the American
                        delegation as Department’s telegram No. 137, February 24, 10 a.m.</note> The
                    elections have resulted in a decisive victory for the Government. The latest
                    figures give the Minseito 273 seats, Seiyukai 174, balance of 19 seats being
                    scattered among various proletarian groups and independents.…</p>
                <p>The Government now has unassailable position and is expected to prosecute its
                    policies both foreign and domestic in a decisive manner.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
